# TypeScript Conventions

Strict mode is enabled project-wide.

## Types

- Avoid `any` - figure out proper types instead
- Prefer interfaces over type aliases
- Avoid enums; use literal types or maps
- Use `Id<"tableName">` for Convex document IDs, not `string`
- Type assertions (`as`) are acceptable when necessary

## Naming

- Use descriptive names with auxiliary verbs: `isLoading`, `hasError`, `canSubmit`
- Directory names: lowercase-dash (e.g., `components/auth-wizard`)

## Functions

- Use `function` keyword for pure functions
- Always specify types for props and return values
- Use async/await for asynchronous code

## Code Quality

When writing code, match the existing style. Avoid:
- Extra comments inconsistent with the file
- Unnecessary defensive checks or try/catch
- Casts to `any` to work around type issues
